manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: 1. If I encounter a problem while using the product, how should I solve it? No matter you encounter any problems, you can contact the seller at any time. The SABLUTE team provides 24-hour online service. 2. How do I use the detachable wrist rest? Both the keyboard and hard wrist rest have built-in magnets. They can be used together or separately. 3. Is there only one USB Receiver? YES! The keyboard and mouse share one USB Receiver. Plug it into the USB port of the computer, wait for the computer to recognize it successfully, and then you can start using it. 4. Do they have a power switch? How long does it take to enter sleep mode? YES! They each have separate power switches (both located on the bottom of the product). They will automatically go to sleep after 10 MINS of inactivity, and you can exit sleep mode by double-clicking any keys. 5. What is included in the package? Are there batteries inside? Batteries not included. The package contains: 1 keyboard, 1 mouse, 1 USB receiver, 1 wrist rest, and 1 manual.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Retro-fun in Pastel Plastic
reviews.reviewText: When I saw this wireless keyboard and mouse that promised to "combine the perfect blend of vintage industrial aesthetics with a modern wireless keyboard," I HAD to have it. I write using a laptop with a damaged keyboard and had struggled with a missing letter for some time. This keyboard was the answer, I was sure of it. I was thrilled when I received the keyboard set.Sadly, the USB receiver was not in the box. I emailed customer service, and was asked to look again. I did so and let them know that I did not find it, just as I knew I would not. I provided my address upon request, as well as my order number. I was then asked to look one more time, and later asked to confirm my address again. Eventually, they agreed to send me a replacement. The whole process of checking, confirming, and promising took about five days. On January 10 I was told that the replacement would arrive in 3-7 business days. I finally received it on January 20.Now that I have it, I am quite pleased with the keyboard and mouse. They are made of a lightweight plastic, and they keys stand out much like a typewriter. They make a clicking sound when I type, which is kind of fun and nostalgic for me, as I was a Secretary for many, many years. The color is fun and makes me happy. The mouse and keyboard work together with one USB receiver. Costwise, this set is a bit pricey, as it is higher than many standard sets. It is less expensive than some high-end or gamer keyboard and mouse combinations.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great product at a great price
reviews.reviewText: I have a laptop with a touch pad and every time I type I come in contact with said touch pad. So of course my cursor goes to random places and it really messes with my flow. So I decided to get a Bluetooth keyboard. I love the color and the raised keys so it can tell you aren’t accidentally hitting two keys at once. It gives off the whole typewriter vibe with the keys. While it doesn’t clack like a typewriter the jets do make a pleasant clicking sound when pressed. It comes with a matching mouse to keep the color vibe consistent.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Gets the job done but if you're used to a GOOD keyboard you'll find it lacking
reviews.reviewText: I've used both gaming and mechanical keyboards, not the highest end but higher than average so this was a change. I think the average keyboard user will be happy with it and if you need a backup keyboard or want to try out round keys then it does the job.Not too loud and doesn't take much pressure to press the keys. They feel faintly gummy and while I can't tell if they actually wobble they leave a sensation of a little jitter back and forth as I'm typing. The mouse clicks are also a little gummy but more in a soft way that I like. Keeps it quiet which is great!Battery powered is a plus for traveling but keep in mind if you want to use this with a phone or tablet you'll need a USB-A converter to whatever type of input your device uses.
